article_title: NASA finally launch new generational moon spacesuit
meta_description:
Astrophysicist and Cosmologist Brad Tucker says NASA’s new generation of spacesuit, made specifically to get astronauts to the moon, has been “in development for quite a few years”. 

“It’s been in development for quite a few years to get astronauts to the moon so when what they’re talking about here is a new type of suit that can be used for lunar explorations. 

“One of the biggest issues they have with the space suits right now is its manoeuvrability essentially because it’s so stiff, astronauts end having health problems and physical body problem,” Mr Tucker told Sky News Australia. 

“So, they’re trying to develop a new one that is safe and effective but obviously easier to use especially compared to what's been used in the past few decades.”
